Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.31,0:00:07.17,Default,Bardalos,0,0,0,,A fine sight indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.17,0:00:08.77,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,It reminds me of old times.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.59,0:00:14.74,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,Towns and people burning,\Nlike in the Dark Age when I was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.74,0:00:17.74,White-Standard,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,500)\pos(348,295)}Lanak    {\fs14}King of Cuscull
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.23,0:00:18.53,Default-Top,Lanak,0,0,0,,A new age is about to dawn on the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.53,0:00:21.69,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,First comes... the Four Great Nations, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.19,0:00:24.27,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,They'll be the first to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.58,0:00:31.59,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,That does it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.92,0:00:38.39,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,So it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.46,0:00:42.17,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Why now, after four hundred years?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.11,0:00:45.77,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,You can rest now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.11,0:00:47.97,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Thanks for all your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.16,0:02:29.00,Ep Title,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(400,1)}~ As the Abyss Is Born ~
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.83,0:02:31.71,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,{\i1}People kill other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.19,0:02:35.67,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's what emotions and power wreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.05,0:02:40.59,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,{\i1}And if that is the consequence, I'd rather \Nshut myself off from love and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:42.47,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'd rather not remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.46,0:02:45.39,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't want to go mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.89,0:02:47.73,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,{\i1}Since, from the very start...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.53,0:02:51.51,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've been engulfed \Nin a madness I cannot escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.62,0:02:55.15,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I hereby define this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.38,0:02:59.85,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Let these words turn to poison by my will.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.38,0:03:03.11,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Sow these seeds to grow into thorns.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.62,0:03:16.62,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.57,0:03:20.49,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Tinasha.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:22.37,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I'm sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.64,0:03:25.49,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,You can sleep after you explain this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.17,0:03:31.10,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I've placed another curse over it,\N so they offset each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.82,0:03:32.72,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.72,0:03:36.32,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,To put it simply, I've broken your curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.32,0:03:38.28,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,You've broken it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.60,0:03:40.54,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,You can clean that off now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.54,0:03:42.62,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Please go take a bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.62,0:03:43.74,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Is this your blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.01,0:03:47.26,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I used it as a catalyst.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.26,0:03:49.41,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Why'd you wait until I was sleeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.41,0:03:51.97,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,It's easier when you're unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.70,0:03:54.83,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Well, I'm off to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:56.42,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.89,0:04:00.06,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Well... thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.62,0:04:14.60,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Why must I attend \NKing Kevin's birthday celebration?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.96,0:04:18.65,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,You call it a ceremony, \Nbut it's little more than a diplomacy ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.33,0:04:21.72,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,If you don't go, who will?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.72,0:04:24.00,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Have fun dealing with those snakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.00,0:04:25.30,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.53,0:04:29.99,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,Your Highness, we've received \Na message from Tayiri.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:32.96,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,It seems Prince Reust won't be able to attend,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.46,0:04:35.84,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,what with the attack from Cuscull.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.84,0:04:39.84,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,Instead, his sister, Princess Cecilia,\Nwill be arriving today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.84,0:04:40.92,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Cuscull?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.92,0:04:42.38,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,An attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.82,0:04:46.59,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,Cuscull mages burned down \Na city near their border.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.98,0:04:52.26,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Tayiri's persecuted mages \Nfor hundreds of years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.26,0:04:55.31,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Is it simply an act of revenge, \Nor something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.13,0:04:58.02,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Tinasha?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.97,0:05:02.10,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.10,0:05:03.07,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.75,0:05:06.53,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Oscar, are you fond of Nark?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.94,0:05:09.99,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Nark is that dragon you keep around, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.36,0:05:14.53,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I'm currently its master, \Nbut I wanted to transfer ownership.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.98,0:05:17.46,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,It looks like Nark's taken a liking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.07,0:05:19.79,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Why so suddenly?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.81,0:05:26.22,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Sure. I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.22,0:05:28.18,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Really? Let me go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.82,0:05:32.93,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Now you're its master.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.93,0:05:33.91,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.59,0:05:43.57,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,How unexpected...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.09,0:05:46.43,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,It's good to shake things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.90,0:05:54.29,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,It's unheard of for a witch \Nto show herself at an event like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:56.75,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I'll keep your identity a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.27,0:06:02.04,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,If you call me your fiancée, \NI'll blow you to bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.70,0:06:04.09,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I'll keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.85,0:06:08.97,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Your Majesty Kevin, Twentieth King of Farsas.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.62,0:06:15.85,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I extend my heartfelt congratulations \Non your fifty-third birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.81,0:06:28.24,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,Your Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:31.24,White-Standard,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,500)\pos(150,295)}Cecelia    {\fs14}Princess of Tayiri
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.83,0:06:30.21,Default-Top,Oscar,0,0,0,,Princess Cecelia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.69,0:06:33.74,Default-Top,Cecelia,0,0,0,,Best wishes on this joyful occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.74,0:06:36.58,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry my brother couldn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.88,0:06:40.04,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,No, I hear your nation has suffered an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.66,0:06:44.53,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,Nothing but a bunch of \Npesky gnats, I assure you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.53,0:06:48.51,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I'd like to hear more about Cuscull, \Nor those gnats as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.51,0:06:49.64,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.64,0:06:52.56,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,Discussing such complicated matters...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.56,0:06:54.72,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,I'd rather not, out here in the open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.29,0:06:59.53,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,Thank you for being so kind as to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.53,0:07:02.44,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,My contract holder \Nis quite persistent, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.44,0:07:04.40,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,It must run in his blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.42,0:07:11.11,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,I don't know how to thank you \Nfor lifting the curse on my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.11,0:07:14.44,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I was just fulfilling the contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.44,0:07:16.85,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Now he can marry anyone he likes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.45,0:07:25.12,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,You must have it rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.12,0:07:26.38,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,I can only imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.91,0:07:29.75,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,You say that like it's none of your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.22,0:07:33.20,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I wish you'd rein him in somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:36.82,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,He won't listen to what I say at his age.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.82,0:07:39.60,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,I'd be happy if you would just marry him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.60,0:07:41.98,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,You won't let that go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.71,0:07:48.21,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:51.13,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Good thing I can't dance in this dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.33,0:07:55.37,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Lanak.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.66,0:08:03.37,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,The embroidery on this dress took \Nten dressmakers half a year to complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.19,0:08:05.44,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.44,0:08:08.31,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,If you're tired, would you like to head to bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.43,0:08:12.25,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,What is it, Tinasha?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.25,0:08:17.05,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,My apologies, but I have important business \Nwith him, so if you would kindly leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.05,0:08:20.02,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,How rude of you to burst in through the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.02,0:08:22.27,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,Your Highness, who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.65,0:08:23.73,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,My wit...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.73,0:08:24.44,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,Wit?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.85,0:08:27.40,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,...filled mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.73,0:08:30.92,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,A lowly mage who doesn't know her place...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.92,0:08:32.18,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,How disgusting!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.18,0:08:32.99,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,Out with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.34,0:08:35.32,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,A lowly mage, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.32,0:08:37.49,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Watch your tongue, you imbecile.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.49,0:08:38.95,Default,Cecelia,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.14,0:08:40.94,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.53,0:08:43.71,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Do you need to be told twice to understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.07,0:08:56.03,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.86,0:09:04.83,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Oscar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:10.23,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I should have died four hundred years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.90,0:09:13.36,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,You mustn't be infatuated with the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.45,0:09:17.32,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Go and accomplish that which you must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.37,0:09:22.66,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Don't forget that the future of this \Nkingdom's people depends on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.57,0:09:25.34,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Tina—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.13,0:09:32.37,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Do you remember what I said \Nwhen I broke Lucrezia's spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.85,0:09:43.74,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,I've come for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.74,0:09:47.35,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,You've grown into a beautiful adult, Aeti.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.35,0:09:48.51,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Lanak!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.10,0:09:50.90,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,You really {\i1}were{\i0} alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.93,0:09:55.05,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,I know you've been searching for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.05,0:09:57.65,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,But I couldn't act for the longest time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.05,0:09:59.13,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.13,0:10:01.87,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,It's more than enough that you're still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.39,0:10:05.72,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,I've started a nation \Ncalled Cuscull for your sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.72,0:10:09.52,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,A fine location, and I've razed \Nall the surrounding cities in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.52,0:10:11.84,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,You will become queen there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.27,0:10:16.01,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,Who's he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.55,0:10:18.47,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I used to have a contract with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.77,0:10:20.80,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,The one who wields the sword Akashia?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:21.93,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,He's a danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.30,0:10:24.79,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Let's leave him be.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.69,0:10:28.81,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Even with its power, it's nothing but a sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.81,0:10:32.22,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,It's of little use if its user lacks strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.22,0:10:35.11,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,What in the world is going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.46,0:10:37.14,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I've broken your curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.14,0:10:39.61,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,My contract with you ends tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.03,0:10:41.62,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,There should still be time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.22,0:10:43.62,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.83,0:10:48.16,Default,Tinasha,0,0,0,,If you're going to hurt Lanak, \Nyou'll have to face me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.15,0:10:54.09,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,{\i1}As I am now, I can kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.54,0:10:55.45,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,{\i1}However...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.30,0:10:58.17,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.69,0:10:59.69,Default,Lanak,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.63,0:11:05.76,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Tinasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.62,0:11:22.10,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,Lady Tinasha...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.97,0:11:25.37,Default,Als,0,0,0,,How's His Highness doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:27.57,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,He's in a foul temper.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.57,0:11:29.83,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,Though he may not look it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.55,0:11:34.42,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.42,0:11:35.33,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,You handle the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.33,0:11:36.66,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.53,0:11:39.72,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,Your Highness, where are you \Ngoing with that sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.18,0:11:41.93,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I'm off to Lucrezia's forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.14,0:11:44.40,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.40,0:11:46.77,Default,Lazar,0,0,0,,What if you run into danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.77,0:11:48.60,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I won't, so it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.60,0:11:50.09,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Let go of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.61,0:11:54.27,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,You can save yourself the trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.68,0:11:56.53,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.63,0:12:02.20,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,I came to see if it was true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.02,0:12:05.14,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Figures that she really did leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.90,0:12:07.61,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,What do you mean, "figures"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.61,0:12:11.00,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Well, I received an invite to Cuscull, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.00,0:12:11.96,Default,Doan,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.30,0:12:14.20,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,I turned them down, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.20,0:12:16.24,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,I imagine the other witches did as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.24,0:12:20.92,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,So her going along will cause \Ntrouble across the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.51,0:12:25.50,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,What relationship do Tinasha \Nand that Lanak fellow have?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.03,0:12:31.01,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,She's been searching for him \Never since she became a witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.01,0:12:33.64,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Good for her, reuniting after so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.64,0:12:36.29,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,But he didn't seem to be in his right mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.29,0:12:38.65,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,It's like he was in a dreamlike haze.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.65,0:12:40.13,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Jealous?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.13,0:12:43.11,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,I don't think that matters, \Nas long as she accepts him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.48,0:12:44.32,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.73,0:12:47.28,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Do you have any right to interfere?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.28,0:12:48.92,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I won't give her up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.92,0:12:52.30,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,She's irreplaceable to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.30,0:12:54.65,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I'll kill that man and bring her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.65,0:12:58.25,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,If she still insists on being with \Nanother man, then I'll let her go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.91,0:13:00.96,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.53,0:13:08.93,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,I'll tell you what she said to me exactly,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.28,0:13:14.64,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,but only to those who are prepared \Nto fight her to the death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.30,0:13:24.03,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.49,0:13:29.61,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Before I tell this story, \Nlet me tell you her real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.61,0:13:30.49,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Her real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.43,0:13:35.75,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Tinasha As Meyer Ur Aeterna Tuldarr.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.08,0:13:37.43,Default,Group,0,0,0,,Tuldarr?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.87,0:13:43.21,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,Isn't Tuldarr the magic empire that was \Ndestroyed overnight four hundred years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.21,0:13:46.42,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,If her last name is the same as that nation...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.03,0:13:48.39,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,That makes her royalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.85,0:13:51.37,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,More precisely, she was \Nthe future queen candidate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.37,0:13:57.35,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Tuldarr was a monarchy, but the ruler was \Ndecided by pure power and not lineage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.94,0:13:59.74,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Decided by power?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.74,0:14:01.82,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,What if an eccentric \Nhappens to be the strongest?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.32,0:14:04.52,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,That's why, as soon as Tinasha was born,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.52,0:14:08.24,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,she was separated from her parents \Nto be raised in the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.02,0:14:12.20,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,Her powers were {\i1}that{\i0} extraordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:15.97,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,So one candidate is chosen each \Nfor king and queen,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.97,0:14:18.16,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,and they end up engaged to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.70,0:14:21.63,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,The boy was the king's only son.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.07,0:14:23.80,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,In other words, Lanak.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.80,0:14:26.59,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,But he was far less powerful than she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.59,0:14:31.49,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Everyone thought Tinasha would be \Nqueen, and Lanak her consort?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.49,0:14:32.30,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.30,0:14:35.26,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Even so, Lanak treated her with great kindness,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.26,0:14:37.60,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,like she was his own sister five years younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.39,0:14:42.01,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,But unbeknownst to them, \Nthe royal court was split into two factions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.99,0:14:46.48,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,The reformists, who called for \Ndiplomacy with foreign nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:51.76,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,The traditionalists, who sought \Nto maintain isolation from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.76,0:14:56.20,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,And with neither side yielding, \Nthe king eventually fell ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.69,0:15:01.17,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Disputes broke out with reformists backing \NTinasha, and traditionalists backing Lanak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.59,0:15:06.38,Default,Als,0,0,0,,You call it a dispute, but wasn't Miss Tinasha \Nguaranteed to accede to the throne?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.38,0:15:10.41,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Yes, which is why the traditionalists \Ncame up with a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.41,0:15:16.35,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,A way to prevent Tinasha's accession \Nand increase Lanak's power all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.41,0:15:19.68,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,It happened when she was thirteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.26,0:15:25.58,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,One night, she opened her eyes to Lanak \Ncarrying her somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.26,0:15:31.46,Flashback,Tinasha,0,0,0,,This is the cathedral...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:33.70,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,Oh, you're awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.70,0:15:38.27,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,You have high magical resistance, \Nso you wake up in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.07,0:15:42.64,Flashback,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Lanak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.64,0:15:44.58,Flashback,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Who are these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.55,0:15:47.89,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,Don't you move, Aeti.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.61,0:15:49.90,Flashback,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Lanak?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.82,0:16:05.27,Flashback,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Lanak... why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.27,0:16:06.73,Flashback,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.73,0:16:11.70,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,We just need to prolong \Nyour life so you don't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.04,0:16:15.16,Flashback,Mage A,0,0,0,,Sacred life, linger here in this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.16,0:16:19.48,Flashback,Mage A,0,0,0,,Let wound remain as wound, \Nblood as blood, smoldering slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.48,0:16:21.62,Flashback,Mage A,0,0,0,,Persist here for some time longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.30,0:16:27.04,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,What I desire is unadulterated power!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.04,0:16:30.71,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,Draw upon this flesh and blood \Nto appear before me, power!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.68,0:16:37.14,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,I'm doing this for Tuldarr, Aeti!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:41.11,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,With this magical power, I will surpass you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.38,0:16:47.66,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.66,0:16:49.10,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,Suppress this at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.59,0:16:54.15,Flashback,Lanak,0,0,0,,A-Any more and...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.76,0:17:28.06,Flashback,Tinasha,0,0,0,,I reign over thee in thy whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.06,0:17:31.32,Flashback,Tinasha,0,0,0,,Take me as thy vessel and obey my command!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.58,0:17:53.89,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,After the whirlwind of \Nmagical power disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.89,0:17:56.59,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,her torn stomach had somehow repaired itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.59,0:17:59.70,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,In exchange, she had to lie there \Nfor three days in unbearable pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.69,0:18:08.26,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,However, after desperately trying to \Nhold onto the magical power,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.26,0:18:11.23,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Tuldarr had already been \Nreduced to a pile of rubble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.54,0:18:15.60,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,The overflowing magic absorbed \Nthe souls of those who had died,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.60,0:18:19.91,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,scattering across the mainland \Nand turning into five magical lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.44,0:18:22.87,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,And after everything had come to pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.33,0:18:25.25,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Tinasha had become a witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.19,0:18:31.91,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,She built a tower in the corner of what \Nhad been Tuldarr territory to live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.47,0:18:35.31,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,And ever since, she's been searching for Lanak.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.75,0:18:38.02,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,I never asked her why, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.74,0:18:41.25,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,That ends my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.25,0:18:49.95,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,How did she feel about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:53.82,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,Don't ask me obvious questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.58,0:18:58.02,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,If she hadn't temporarily sealed away \Nyour defensive barrier with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.76,0:19:01.38,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,do you think Lanak would have let you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.87,0:19:04.33,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,And she left her dragon with you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.77,0:19:07.12,Default,Lucrezia,0,0,0,,The answer's right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.48,0:19:12.66,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,This doesn't change our plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.66,0:19:16.55,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I'll kill that revolting man \Nand bring Tinasha back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.85,0:19:17.87,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,That's all there is to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.02,0:19:28.74,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,We've received a letter from Cuscull.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.74,0:19:33.52,Default,Nessan,0,0,0,,"To the Four Great Nations: \NTayiri, Cezar, Gandona, and Farsas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.52,0:19:34.73,White-Standard,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,500)\pos(150,295)}Kumu    {\fs14}Farsas Chief Mage
Dialogue: 1,0:19:33.52,0:19:34.73,White-Standard,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,500)\pos(465,295)}Granfort    {\fs14}Farsas General
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.86,0:19:35.93,Default-Top,Nessan,0,0,0,,We hereby demand your capitulation."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.44,0:19:38.23,White-Standard,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,500)\pos(460,295)}Nessan    {\fs14}Farsas Minister of the Interior
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.44,0:19:41.65,Default-Top,Nessan,0,0,0,,A few days ago, Tayiri led a large army \Nof ten thousand men into Cuscull.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.47,0:19:45.87,Default-Top,Nessan,0,0,0,,However, Tayiri's forces \Nwere practically wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.87,0:19:47.66,White-Standard,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,500)\pos(225,295)}Bardalos    {\fs14}Cuscull Chief Mage
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.26,0:19:50.87,Default-Top,Nessan,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Cuscull lost less than \Nfifty of their mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.87,0:19:52.72,Default,Nessan,0,0,0,,That's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.72,0:19:56.70,Default,Nessan,0,0,0,,Five large cities in Tayiri \Nwere devastated at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.70,0:20:00.59,Default,Nessan,0,0,0,,with thousands losing their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.29,0:20:04.24,Default,Nessan,0,0,0,,In the affected cities, \Nthe buildings were left intact,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.24,0:20:06.55,Default,Nessan,0,0,0,,with all of their citizens vanishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.23,0:20:09.09,Default,Nessan,0,0,0,,The one responsible...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.09,0:20:11.27,Default,Nessan,0,0,0,,appears to be the Witch of the Azure Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.38,0:20:18.19,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,And while Farsas has received \Na request for aid...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.66,0:20:23.32,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,Oscar, they've additionally asked \Nfor you to slay the witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.32,0:20:24.16,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.71,0:20:27.12,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I'm the only one who can kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.30,0:20:29.70,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,But I won't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.65,0:20:34.81,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,If Tayiri is asking for aid, \Nwe should head there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.81,0:20:38.54,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,But that's only if you're treating \NCuscull as the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.54,0:20:40.13,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,She's a different story.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.53,0:20:44.09,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,Hasn't she gone to Cuscull of her own will?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.46,0:20:47.30,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I don't think the truth lies \Nin only what we can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.30,0:20:49.08,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,Have you been taken in by the witch?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.08,0:20:50.52,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,You damn fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.89,0:20:54.56,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten that our people's \Nlives rest on your shoulders?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.33,0:20:57.33,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Dear father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.33,0:20:59.08,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,There's no need for further discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.08,0:21:00.86,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I've already made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.86,0:21:04.36,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I don't plan on losing, or forsaking anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.10,0:21:10.83,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,Maybe it does run in the blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.99,0:21:13.41,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.41,0:21:15.48,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,Do as you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.48,0:21:16.54,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,In exchange...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:20.08,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,You take the throne as king.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.08,0:21:22.21,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,It's about time I stepped down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.21,0:21:23.55,Default,Nessan,0,0,0,,Y-Your Majesty!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.85,0:21:26.50,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,It may be a bit early, \Nbut that shouldn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.50,0:21:29.01,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,Take this opportunity \Nto learn all that you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.57,0:21:35.20,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I swear...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.20,0:21:37.62,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,Everyone loves putting me through the wringer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.95,0:21:39.96,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.96,0:21:42.48,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,I'll gladly accede to the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.37,0:21:48.38,Default,Kevin,0,0,0,,Always keep in mind that your actions \Ndecide the fate of this kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.36,0:21:53.89,Flashback,Tinasha,0,0,0,,{\i1}As long as you wield that sword, \Nand I remain a witch,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.67,0:21:57.50,Flashback,Tinasha,0,0,0,,{\i1}someday you might really have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.50,0:22:01.01,Default,Oscar,0,0,0,,{\i1}I won't forget those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.51,0:23:39.98,Next Ep Title,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,1)}~ The End of the Dream ~
